main event: Multiple reports of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) observed near a missile site in Nebraska
interesting points: Five successive observations were made of a peculiar object that moved silently and slowly towards the northwest, changing from yellowish-white to green and white lights

Sergeants and two neighbors observed an oblong object about 50 feet long, 15 feet wide, and 15-20 feet high, moving slowly easterly with white and green lights, seen for approximately 3 minutes before disappearing to the north
A group of eight young civilians observed an object near Cheyenne, Wyoming that appeared to move slowly westward and then disappear, giving off a pulsating type of light and seeming dark and nebulous
A SSgt first sighted the object, then informed two base members and the Base Commander, who attempted to launch a Falcon M-192 missile but was unable to do so
Members of the Civil Engineering Geodetic Survey and the Sonar crew from a local naval training center observed an unidentified object moving at a high rate of speed towards the east-southeast
result: Inconclusive, some cases eliminated as natural phenomena
sighted object: Oblong objects, bright lights, dark nebulous shapes
photographs: No photographs present in the document
